OL,6,FIn the witness box, Mr Adams said he
OL,7,F"liked" and "knew" Mr Donaldson, but
OL,8,Fdid not have many dealings with him.
OL,10,FBeginning his cross-examination on
OL,11,FFriday afternoon, Paul Gallagher SC
OL,12,Fasked Mr Adams if he remembered how
OL,13,Fmany people were killed in various
OL,14,Fatrocities during The Troubles.
OL,16,FMr Adams told the hearing he did not
OL,17,Fremember how many people were killed
OL,18,Fin incidents such as Bloody Friday or
OL,19,Fthe Claudy bombings, and asked what it
OL,20,Fhad to do with Mr Donaldson.
